OL,3,C'Crisis' in Welsh schools over levels
OL,4,Cof violence and abuse at teachers
OL,6,FTeachers' allegations include being
OL,7,Fshoved or barged, hit or punched,
OL,8,Fkicked, spat at, and head-butted,
OL,9,Fwhile others reported having chairs
OL,10,Fthrown at them.
OL,12,FA union official claims teachers are
OL,13,F"operating in a hostile environment
OL,14,Fwhere they cannot teach and pupils
OL,15,Fcannot learn", saying many are leaving
OL,16,Fthe profession.
OL,18,FThe Welsh Government says there is a
OL,19,Fduty on local authorities and schools
OL,20,Fto ensure schools are a safe
OL,21,Fenvironment for all.
