OL,3,C'Crisis' in Welsh schools over levels
OL,4,Cof violence and abuse at teachers
OL,6,FDr Patrick Roach, NASUWT general
OL,7,Fsecretary, said: "We do not accept a
OL,8,Fsituation in which teachers in Wales
OL,9,Ffeel abandoned by their employers or
OL,10,Fby the Welsh Government and left alone
OL,11,Fto deal with serious episodes of pupil
OL,12,Findiscipline and violence.
OL,14,F"Teachers did not sign up to become
OL,15,Fpunch bags or referees in physical
OL,16,Faltercations between pupils. They have
OL,17,Fa right to feel and to be safe at work.
OL,1,Wj5hw}j5 ~shws                   G3/7
